  "methodology": {
    "link": "Methodology",
    "title": "Methodology",
    "body": "Reported (official) emissions are the World Bank deforestation figures. Full accounting adds the forgone carbon sink — the future sequestration lost when forest is cleared — estimated as an R factor times cumulative area loss. R combines an aboveground rate with a locked allometric factor of 1.24; the conservative / mid / high band reflects its uncertainty. Estimates are dashed; measured values are solid. Composite figures start in 2000 (stock coverage) while the sink integral runs from 1990."
  },
